    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="157"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                <head>157. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station in Guatemala</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d157fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 142, Folder 4. Priority; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. No time of transmittal
                        appears on the telegram. Repeated to the Director of Central
                        Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-20">May 20, 1954</date>.</dateline>
                <p>2890. Ref: GUAT 602.<note n="2" xml:id="d157fn2">Not printed. (Ibid., Box 11,
                        Folder 2)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Inadvisable disclose our relationship with ESQUIRE to <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName>, especially in view [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>]–<persName corresp="#p_CJH1"
                            >Calligeris</persName> hostility. Basic compartmentation between
                            <persName corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName> and <gloss
                            target="#t_KPROGRAM1">K–Program</gloss> must be kept.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Assure ESQUIRE we will keep him out of <persName corresp="#p_CJH1"
                            >Calligeris</persName> black book at proper time.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> not contacting <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName> on this matter. Will inform you
                        if <persName corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName> volunteers
                        anything.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>ESQUIRE not to disclose any operational details to [<hi rend="italic">name
                            not declassified</hi>].</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Keep ESQUIRE in <gloss target="#t_WSBURNT1">WSBURNT</gloss> as long as
                        operationally necessary and feasible.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
